Raspadskaya Rises for Second Day on Report of Stake Sale to VEB

-- B y   J a s o n   C o r c o r a n
-- 
2011-07-13T07:29:31Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-13/raspadskaya-rises-for-second-day-on-report-of-stake-sale-to-veb.html
OAO Raspadskaya, a Russian coal
producer, climbed for a second day after Interfax reported
yesterday state-run VEB bank may pay $5.3 billion for an 80
percent stake.  The stock added as much as 3.6 percent and last traded 2.2
percent higher at 182.47 rubles by 11:14 a.m. in Moscow. Its
shares jumped 2.8 percent yesterday.  The $5.3 billion price implies a premium of about 36
percent to the current market value of the company, according to
Dmitry Smolin, an equity analyst at UralSib Financial Corp. in
Moscow. The deal may be approved at VEBâ€™s supervisory board
meeting scheduled for today, Smolin sad in e-mailed report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
